### Code Modification

The current implementation uses a simplistic check (`includes('@')`) which fails to validate the full email structure, potentially causing downstream database serialization errors or logic failures when special characters like `+` are present in the local part of the email. The fix involves implementing a robust regular expression to validate the email format before attempting to save.

```javascript
// Updated function with robust email validation
function updateProfile(email, name) {
  // Regex for standard email validation allowing special characters like + in local part
  const emailRegex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/;

  if (emailRegex.test(email)) {
    saveToDB(email, name);
  } else {
    throw new Error('Invalid email format');
  }
}
```

